241
00:13:50,220 --> 00:13:54,050
We are now the emergency service
for the emergency services.

242
00:13:54,100 --> 00:13:55,450
Yeah, we are. That's what we are.

243
00:13:55,500 --> 00:13:57,930
Quite a lot of people have written
to us and said, "Right,

244
00:13:57,980 --> 00:14:00,450
"when are you going to
improve fire engines?"

245
00:14:00,500 --> 00:14:02,970
Mm! No, but there's
a... No, actually...

246
00:14:03,020 --> 00:14:05,210
We've looked into this
and there's a problem,

247
00:14:05,260 --> 00:14:07,770
because if you have to build
a vehicle big enough for all

248
00:14:07,820 --> 00:14:11,050
the water you need and pumps
and ladders and buckets

249
00:14:11,100 --> 00:14:15,330
and six burly men, and
women, in Wellingtons,

250
00:14:15,380 --> 00:14:17,810
what you end up with
is a fire engine.

251
00:14:17,860 --> 00:14:20,930
~ Yeah.
~ But, specifically, a British
fire engine. That's important.

252
00:14:20,980 --> 00:14:23,290
Yeah, not one of those stupid
American ones where all

253
00:14:23,340 --> 00:14:25,170
~ the firemen stand on the outside.
~ They do!

254
00:14:25,220 --> 00:14:28,170
So you get there and there's nobody
on board to put the fire out!

255
00:14:28,220 --> 00:14:31,330
Do you know what I like about
the British fire engine?

256
00:14:31,380 --> 00:14:33,780
It says "Dennis" on the front.

257
00:14:34,300 --> 00:14:36,250
Dennis is a reassuring name.

258
00:14:36,300 --> 00:14:40,210
A Dennis would remember
to return your lawn mower.

259
00:14:40,260 --> 00:14:43,970
It is interesting, actually, because American
fire engines have really stupid names.

260
00:14:44,020 --> 00:14:46,170
I've got a picture of an
American fire engine here.

261
00:14:46,220 --> 00:14:48,610
~ Guess what that's called?
~ Fire Engine.

262
00:14:48,660 --> 00:14:51,010
No, it's called The Igniter.

263
00:14:51,060 --> 00:14:53,890
~ LAUGHTER
~ It is!

264
00:14:53,940 --> 00:14:57,570
~ How does...? "I've already got a fire!"
~ Exactly!

265
00:14:57,620 --> 00:14:59,330
It should be called The Extinguisher.

266
00:14:59,380 --> 00:15:02,090
~ They've probably got an ambulance
called The Haemorrhage.
~ Yes.

267
00:15:02,140 --> 00:15:04,330
~ LAUGHTER
~ Right, earlier on, James

268
00:15:04,380 --> 00:15:08,010
had a go at a proper road
test in a one-off car show

269
00:15:08,060 --> 00:15:11,250
~ and now it's my turn.
~ Try not to muck it up.

270
00:15:11,300 --> 00:15:14,930
No, no, no, relax, this is going
to be a blizzard of facts

271
00:15:14,980 --> 00:15:18,650
because I'm going to talk
about the new BMW M3.

272
00:15:18,700 --> 00:15:23,050
It has a smaller engine
than the old model,

273
00:15:23,100 --> 00:15:24,770
three litres rather than four.

274
00:15:24,820 --> 00:15:28,730
It has two fewer cylinders,
but it is turbo-charged,

275
00:15:28,780 --> 00:15:33,690
so you get a little bit more
horsepower and 111 more torques.

276
00:15:33,740 --> 00:15:37,170
That means it's four
seconds a lap faster

277
00:15:37,220 --> 00:15:39,730
round our track than the old car.

278
00:15:39,780 --> 00:15:43,090
And four seconds is a huge
gulf because, remember,

279
00:15:43,140 --> 00:15:46,170
that was already five
seconds a lap faster

280
00:15:46,220 --> 00:15:47,650
round the Ascari track in Spain

281
00:15:47,700 --> 00:15:49,570
than the equivalent
Mercedes and Audi,

282
00:15:49,620 --> 00:15:54,050
so this is properly quick
AND it's more economical,

283
00:15:54,100 --> 00:15:56,370
but, and this is the big one,

284
00:15:56,420 --> 00:15:58,420
is it nicer to drive?

285
00:16:04,620 --> 00:16:07,370
Well, here it is, slithering
about on our track.

286
00:16:07,420 --> 00:16:09,570
TYRES SCREECH

287
00:16:09,620 --> 00:16:13,940
Look at that. I mean, that's
just... the M3 signature dish.

288
00:16:16,140 --> 00:16:19,850
But, straightaway, I must tell
you there is a bit of a niggle.

289
00:16:19,900 --> 00:16:22,210
~ TYRES SCREECH
~ If you stick the tail out

290
00:16:22,260 --> 00:16:26,610
in a corner, which you can,
easily, because it's an M3,

291
00:16:26,660 --> 00:16:30,650
you'll find it very
hard to hold the drift

292
00:16:30,700 --> 00:16:35,300
because the power steering is now
electric rather than hydraulic.

293
00:16:38,060 --> 00:16:39,970
Going round a corner like this

294
00:16:40,020 --> 00:16:43,490
is like wrestling with the tail
of an excitable crocodile.

295
00:16:43,540 --> 00:16:45,730
It's not just hard to hold the slide,

296
00:16:45,780 --> 00:16:49,490
it's also hard to straighten
up again afterwards.

297
00:16:49,540 --> 00:16:51,280
See what I mean?

298
00:16:53,460 --> 00:16:56,050
Now, I admit, in the real world,

299
00:16:56,100 --> 00:16:59,010
this isn't going to be
much of a problem...

300
00:16:59,060 --> 00:17:01,050
ever, if I'm honest.

301
00:17:01,100 --> 00:17:03,810
And anyway, you can solve
it by taking the steering

302
00:17:03,860 --> 00:17:08,970
out of Sport Plus mode and
putting it in Comfort mode.

303
00:17:09,020 --> 00:17:11,160
Then everything is fine.

304
00:17:18,220 --> 00:17:20,090
Oh, yeah!

305
00:17:20,140 --> 00:17:22,210
In fact, everything
is more than fine,

306
00:17:22,260 --> 00:17:26,020
everything is absolutely sublime!

307
00:17:31,420 --> 00:17:34,850
I'm not going to beat about
the bush, this car is...

308
00:17:34,900 --> 00:17:36,170
utterly brilliant.

309
00:17:36,220 --> 00:17:39,370
It's well made, it's
got seating for four,

310
00:17:39,420 --> 00:17:44,010
it's got a decent-sized boot,
it's comfortable, it's quiet,

311
00:17:44,060 --> 00:17:46,730
it's got lots of standard equipment.

312
00:17:47,980 --> 00:17:52,490
In many ways, this car
is like the perfect dog -

313
00:17:52,540 --> 00:17:55,050
it's loyal, it's cute,
it doesn't chase sheep,

314
00:17:55,100 --> 00:17:56,970
it doesn't go wrong all the time

315
00:17:57,020 --> 00:18:00,130
and yet, if a burglar
comes, it has the power

316
00:18:00,180 --> 00:18:02,460
to rip his throat out.

317
00:18:04,180 --> 00:18:07,490
"Look at me! I'm an attack dog now!

318
00:18:07,540 --> 00:18:10,060
"I'm fierce and bitey!"

319
00:18:13,900 --> 00:18:16,210
And that really is that.

320
00:18:16,260 --> 00:18:18,930
It is a fabulous, wonderful car

321
00:18:18,980 --> 00:18:21,610
and if you have £56,000 lying around,

322
00:18:21,660 --> 00:18:24,130
you should buy one immediately.

323
00:18:25,580 --> 00:18:27,250
Or should you?

324
00:18:28,020 --> 00:18:31,010
Because today, we live
in strange times.

325
00:18:31,060 --> 00:18:33,050
Environmental times.

326
00:18:33,100 --> 00:18:37,130
And BMW has another new
car which reflects that.

327
00:18:37,180 --> 00:18:42,060
It's one of the most talked-about
cars in years and this is it.

328
00:18:46,060 --> 00:18:49,490
It's called the i8 and it's a hybrid,

329
00:18:49,540 --> 00:18:52,170
which means it's powered
by an electric motor

330
00:18:52,220 --> 00:18:59,130
and a tiny three cylinder, 1.5 litre,
turbo-charged petrol engine.

331
00:18:59,180 --> 00:19:02,050
That doesn't sound
like much of a recipe.

332
00:19:02,100 --> 00:19:05,410
It sounds like a sort of
glorified Toyota Prius,

333
00:19:05,460 --> 00:19:08,970
but let me give you
the headline figures.

334
00:19:09,020 --> 00:19:12,610
This car does 155mph

335
00:19:12,660 --> 00:19:16,970
and 134 miles to the gallon.

336
00:19:17,020 --> 00:19:20,570
And because it's so economical,

337
00:19:20,620 --> 00:19:23,690
you get a £5,000 grant from
the government if you buy one,

338
00:19:23,740 --> 00:19:26,370
it's exempt from the
London Congestion Charge

339
00:19:26,420 --> 00:19:29,090
and the road-tax bill,
as you can see here, is...

340
00:19:29,140 --> 00:19:30,340
nil.

341
00:19:33,740 --> 00:19:34,930
It really does sound, then,

342
00:19:34,980 --> 00:19:39,610
like this car answers everyone's
prayers, but does it?

343
00:19:39,660 --> 00:19:43,370
Are pure-bred petrolheads
like me really going to say,

344
00:19:43,420 --> 00:19:48,620
"Mm, yes, what I really want next
is a three-cylinder hybrid?"

345
00:19:50,180 --> 00:19:53,370
Well, that is what I'm
going to try and find out.

346
00:19:53,420 --> 00:19:56,570
I'm going to set the satellite
navigation for Whitby

347
00:19:56,620 --> 00:19:59,610
in North Yorkshire and, obviously,
in a car as futuristic as this,

348
00:19:59,660 --> 00:20:01,610
you don't push buttons to do that,

349
00:20:01,660 --> 00:20:04,690
you trace the letters you
want on this pad here,

350
00:20:04,740 --> 00:20:06,820
so, wuh...

351
00:20:08,420 --> 00:20:09,820
.. huh...

352
00:20:10,900 --> 00:20:11,970
.. ih...

353
00:20:12,020 --> 00:20:13,580
tuh...

354
00:20:14,580 --> 00:20:17,170
Ah-ha! OK.

355
00:20:17,220 --> 00:20:20,810
'Whitby, North Yorkshire,
guidance started.'

356
00:20:20,860 --> 00:20:23,650
Now, the reason I've
chosen Whitby is,

357
00:20:23,700 --> 00:20:26,450
A, you get the best fish and
chips and the world there

358
00:20:26,500 --> 00:20:30,650
and, B, the M3 we saw earlier
is waiting for me there,

359
00:20:30,700 --> 00:20:35,090
which means, when I arrive,
I will face a simple choice.

360
00:20:35,140 --> 00:20:38,900
Will I want to drive
home in that or this?

361
00:20:42,500 --> 00:20:46,010
With the sat nav looking for the
most economical route to Whitby,

362
00:20:46,060 --> 00:20:48,330
I put my sensible head
on and settled down

363
00:20:48,380 --> 00:20:51,940
for a 200 mile fact-finding mission.

364
00:20:54,340 --> 00:20:58,370
You have a choice of
three driving modes.

365
00:20:58,420 --> 00:21:00,410
Number one, electric drive.

366
00:21:00,460 --> 00:21:02,850
That's the electric motor only.

367
00:21:02,900 --> 00:21:07,650
It gives you a range of 20 miles,
19 more than you get from a Prius

368
00:21:07,700 --> 00:21:11,180
and probably enough for you
to do your morning commute.

369
00:21:12,580 --> 00:21:14,530
Then, if you move the
gear lever over here,

370
00:21:14,580 --> 00:21:17,890
you engage sport mode and that
means the electric motor

371
00:21:17,940 --> 00:21:22,330
and the petrol engine are working
together to give 352 horsepower

372
00:21:22,380 --> 00:21:26,620
and it makes the car sort of
firm and bitey and Nurburgringy.

373
00:21:29,620 --> 00:21:34,780
But, since we are on the A1,
I shall go for... comfort mode.

374
00:21:36,460 --> 00:21:37,800
Lovely.

375
00:21:38,540 --> 00:21:41,490
'And it really was lovely.'

376
00:21:41,540 --> 00:21:45,050
I know there is an electric
motor in the front,

377
00:21:45,100 --> 00:21:49,010
driving the front wheels through
a two-speed automatic gearbox.

378
00:21:49,060 --> 00:21:51,730
I know there's a petrol
engine at the back,

379
00:21:51,780 --> 00:21:55,210
driving the rear wheels through
a six-speed automatic gearbox.

380
00:21:55,260 --> 00:21:59,770
I also know there is another small
electric motor at the back,

381
00:21:59,820 --> 00:22:03,340
filling in the gaps and doing
all sorts of clever things.

382
00:22:04,420 --> 00:22:06,930
And yet, sitting here,

383
00:22:06,980 --> 00:22:12,770
this car feels no weirder
to drive than that...

384
00:22:12,820 --> 00:22:16,450
whatever it is, that
hatchback thing there.

385
00:22:16,500 --> 00:22:19,410
I've got a steering wheel,
gear lever, accelerator,

386
00:22:19,460 --> 00:22:23,010
brake and Ken Bruce on the radio.

387
00:22:23,060 --> 00:22:25,250
How normal is that?!

388
00:22:25,300 --> 00:22:28,890
♪ BBC Radio 2! ♪

389
00:22:28,940 --> 00:22:30,930
But there is a problem.

390
00:22:30,980 --> 00:22:35,250
If you're driving in comfort mode,
you're not really charging up

391
00:22:35,300 --> 00:22:39,300
the batteries and, eventually,
they are going to go flat.

392
00:22:40,780 --> 00:22:43,370
One solution is to
turn off the motorway

393
00:22:43,420 --> 00:22:45,490
and charge them up at the mains,

394
00:22:45,540 --> 00:22:49,500
but, as you're about to see,
this is not to be recommended.

395
00:22:58,660 --> 00:23:01,370
"Connect your vehicle and validate."

396
00:23:01,420 --> 00:23:04,490
Look, I can operate a Hoover!

397
00:23:04,540 --> 00:23:07,370
Oh, this is stupid!

398
00:23:07,420 --> 00:23:12,580
Well, it must... It must be
charging. It's plugged in, so...

399
00:23:14,700 --> 00:23:17,370
I shall go and get a cup of coffee.

400
00:23:20,300 --> 00:23:23,530
While we wait for the batteries
to charge, let me show you

401
00:23:23,580 --> 00:23:26,890
this incredible app that you
can get with your i8, OK?

402
00:23:26,940 --> 00:23:30,250
If I push that, I can
set the air conditioning

403
00:23:30,300 --> 00:23:33,340
so the car is cool when
I get back into it.

404
00:23:34,820 --> 00:23:36,690
How amazing is that?!

405
00:23:36,740 --> 00:23:38,290
If I can also flash the headlights,

406
00:23:38,340 --> 00:23:41,570
so I could find it if I've lost
it in a car park. I can lock it.

407
00:23:41,620 --> 00:23:43,330
I can unlock it.

408
00:23:43,380 --> 00:23:46,610
I don't know why you'd want to
do that remotely, but you can.

409
00:23:46,660 --> 00:23:50,250
I wouldn't be at all surprised
to find a feature on here

410
00:23:50,300 --> 00:23:54,340
that enables the i8 to find
another i8 for a good time.

411
00:23:55,540 --> 00:23:58,130
'After an hour, I
went back to the car

412
00:23:58,180 --> 00:24:01,810
'and found that the charging
point hadn't worked.'

413
00:24:01,860 --> 00:24:08,090
If you had a pure electric car,
you would be completely stuffed,

414
00:24:08,140 --> 00:24:10,810
but this is not a pure electric car.

415
00:24:11,860 --> 00:24:13,400
So I'm not.

416
00:24:16,380 --> 00:24:19,090
I can either drive along
without the batteries

417
00:24:19,140 --> 00:24:23,930
or I can put the gear lever
over here to engage sport mode

418
00:24:23,980 --> 00:24:28,260
and then they are being charged
up as I drive along.

419
00:24:30,820 --> 00:24:33,980
What's more, in sport mode,
the i8 is properly fast.

420
00:24:36,300 --> 00:24:39,330
I scoffed when BMW said they
were going to make a hybrid

421
00:24:39,380 --> 00:24:42,820
that was as fast as a 911 or
a Chevrolet Corvette, but...

422
00:24:44,500 --> 00:24:46,240
.. it really is!

423
00:24:47,740 --> 00:24:50,740
'It's so fast that soon
I was in the North.'

424
00:24:52,940 --> 00:24:56,370
This is Doncaster. This
is where I grew up.

425
00:24:56,420 --> 00:24:59,810
It was a mining town
back then, but now look.

426
00:24:59,860 --> 00:25:01,860
It's a wind farm.

427
00:25:03,260 --> 00:25:07,340
Bit less romantic, the windmills,
and they employ fewer people, but...

428
00:25:09,020 --> 00:25:11,100
Time moves on, I guess.

429
00:25:12,420 --> 00:25:15,450
'So far, then, the i8 had done well.

430
00:25:15,500 --> 00:25:20,010
'But to find out if it could truly
win the heart of the petrol head,

431
00:25:20,060 --> 00:25:22,650
'I turned off the A1 and plunged into

432
00:25:22,700 --> 00:25:25,690
'the beautiful North
Yorkshire Moors.'

433
00:25:25,740 --> 00:25:28,780
DRAMATIC, SWEEPING MUSIC

434
00:25:41,620 --> 00:25:43,490
So, let's find out.

435
00:25:48,580 --> 00:25:50,920
Oh, God above, this is good!

436
00:25:55,580 --> 00:25:57,620
This is a revelation!

437
00:26:06,260 --> 00:26:09,690
It's the lightness that
staggers you most of all.

438
00:26:09,740 --> 00:26:14,060
It's almost as though I'm steering
using nothing but thought.

439
00:26:16,300 --> 00:26:20,050
And because the heavy battery pack
is located in the middle of the car,

440
00:26:20,100 --> 00:26:25,050
here, low down, it has the
same centre of gravity as...

441
00:26:25,100 --> 00:26:26,740
as a worm!

442
00:26:28,380 --> 00:26:32,850
Couple that to the
four-wheel-drive system and, honestly,

443
00:26:32,900 --> 00:26:37,580
you can go round any corner at
any speed that takes your fancy.

444
00:26:39,220 --> 00:26:43,170
The harder I go, the faster I drive,

445
00:26:43,220 --> 00:26:45,130
the sharper I brake,

446
00:26:45,180 --> 00:26:48,860
the more electricity I'm
making for the batteries.

447
00:26:49,940 --> 00:26:51,850
If you get busted for
speeding in this car,

448
00:26:51,900 --> 00:26:54,330
you get a thank-you letter
from Greenpeace.

449
00:26:54,380 --> 00:26:56,120
And rightly so!

450
00:26:57,460 --> 00:27:00,930
'But before we get carried away
with this environmental stuff,

451
00:27:00,980 --> 00:27:04,660
'there's one important point
we all need to remember.'

452
00:27:06,700 --> 00:27:11,130
I've always had a fundamental
problem with hybrids.

453
00:27:11,180 --> 00:27:12,850
And it's this.

454
00:27:13,780 --> 00:27:16,690
We all know the world
has limited resources

455
00:27:16,740 --> 00:27:20,010
and we must do all we
can to eke them out.

456
00:27:20,060 --> 00:27:21,930
And you're not going to do that

457
00:27:21,980 --> 00:27:26,170
if you drive around in a car that
has, effectively, two engines.

458
00:27:26,220 --> 00:27:29,970
You don't solve the problem
of conspicuous consumption

459
00:27:30,020 --> 00:27:33,490
by using conspicuous consumption.

460
00:27:33,540 --> 00:27:34,970
The thing is, though,

461
00:27:35,020 --> 00:27:38,610
while you have to rape the
world to make a car like that,

462
00:27:38,660 --> 00:27:40,970
the benefits of owning
one for you and I,

463
00:27:41,020 --> 00:27:44,460
in the here and now, are
immense, because that car...

464
00:27:45,820 --> 00:27:47,890
That car is staggering.

465
00:27:48,900 --> 00:27:50,650
It's breathtaking.

466
00:27:50,700 --> 00:27:54,330
MUSIC: The Hovis Theme, New
World Symphony by Dvorak

467
00:27:54,380 --> 00:27:57,320
It's nearly as
breathtaking as that view.

468
00:28:03,580 --> 00:28:08,130
'With the advert for Yorkshire
over, I got back on the road.'

469
00:28:08,180 --> 00:28:09,730
It is incredible to think

470
00:28:09,780 --> 00:28:15,250
that I'm now cruising into Whitby
in silent electric mode,

471
00:28:15,300 --> 00:28:20,890
using electricity that I made
by driving quickly on the moors.

472
00:28:20,940 --> 00:28:24,130
The message really is very
clear from this car.

473
00:28:24,180 --> 00:28:27,500
If you want to save the
planet, drive fast.

