899
00:52:49,860 --> 00:52:52,250
'Next time you're late for work

900
00:52:52,300 --> 00:52:54,770
'it's worth remembering that nothing

901
00:52:54,820 --> 00:52:58,620
'but nothing gets in the
way of a Land Rover.'

902
00:53:02,300 --> 00:53:04,650
Now, the thing is...

903
00:53:04,700 --> 00:53:08,770
that advert, as exciting as
it looked, was, I'm afraid,

904
00:53:08,820 --> 00:53:11,210
the result of... shall we say,

905
00:53:11,260 --> 00:53:12,970
the magic of television,

906
00:53:13,020 --> 00:53:16,850
because the Land Rover
didn't winch itself up.

907
00:53:16,900 --> 00:53:20,090
The winch on the front bumper
pulled it the first few feet

908
00:53:20,140 --> 00:53:21,890
out of the water,

909
00:53:21,940 --> 00:53:24,770
but then it was actually hauled
the rest of the way up

910
00:53:24,820 --> 00:53:28,140
by a much bigger winch hidden
at the top of the dam.

911
00:53:29,300 --> 00:53:32,930
So I think you can probably
see what's coming next.

912
00:53:32,980 --> 00:53:35,650
As our tribute to the
Land Rover Defender

913
00:53:35,700 --> 00:53:39,220
we are going to redo
that stunt properly.

914
00:53:44,100 --> 00:53:46,220
Oh... God.

915
00:53:48,380 --> 00:53:52,380
The dam I'll be climbing
is Claerwen in Wales.

916
00:53:53,420 --> 00:53:56,210
It's 1,200 feet wide and,

917
00:53:56,260 --> 00:54:00,410
more worryingly for
me, 200 feet high.

918
00:54:00,460 --> 00:54:03,050
To make things worse,

919
00:54:03,100 --> 00:54:06,930
the Land Rover I'll be
using is 64 years old.

920
00:54:06,980 --> 00:54:11,730
So, in order to do what they
never managed in the TV advert,

921
00:54:11,780 --> 00:54:14,260
we've added some bits.

922
00:54:16,180 --> 00:54:19,930
When they made that advert there
wasn't a winch around big enough

923
00:54:19,980 --> 00:54:23,930
to take on board all the cable
you need to go up a big dam.

924
00:54:23,980 --> 00:54:27,210
So we - well, not Jeremy
and me, somebody else -

925
00:54:27,260 --> 00:54:29,700
has built this ginormous one.

926
00:54:30,820 --> 00:54:34,450
Then there's the matter
of the engine.

927
00:54:34,500 --> 00:54:39,650
You see, when this thing starts to
go up the dam it will go vertical,

928
00:54:39,700 --> 00:54:44,010
and at that point the engine
at the front will cut out.

929
00:54:44,060 --> 00:54:47,090
Problem, because we need the
engine to power the winch.

930
00:54:47,140 --> 00:54:49,410
Solution...

931
00:54:49,460 --> 00:54:51,570
a second engine just for the winch.

932
00:54:51,620 --> 00:54:54,530
Best of all this is
built so it can pivot.

933
00:54:54,580 --> 00:54:58,090
As the Land Rover goes
vertical this stays level.

934
00:54:58,140 --> 00:55:02,090
None of this gave me
much comfort, however,

935
00:55:02,140 --> 00:55:04,740
when I was standing at the bottom.

936
00:55:05,980 --> 00:55:07,930
Oh, bloody hell.

