It's much steeper

938
00:55:10,140 --> 00:55:13,770
than the other dam in the advert.

939
00:55:13,820 --> 00:55:17,490
For a brief moment I thought
I was off the hook

940
00:55:17,540 --> 00:55:20,730
because the start point looked
completely inaccessible.

941
00:55:20,780 --> 00:55:24,570
Sadly, the producers
had thought of that.

942
00:55:24,620 --> 00:55:26,780
I hate problem solvers.

943
00:55:29,660 --> 00:55:32,530
And this is just a
little amuse-bouche.

944
00:55:33,340 --> 00:55:36,170
Eventually, I was in place.

945
00:55:36,220 --> 00:55:39,540
The winch cable was
attached to the top.

946
00:55:42,500 --> 00:55:45,100
And it was time to begin.

947
00:55:46,620 --> 00:55:50,210
That's the engine in the back
that powers the winch, remember,

948
00:55:50,260 --> 00:55:51,610
cos of the angle.

949
00:55:51,660 --> 00:55:54,730
Um... I'd love to think of
something else to say or do.

950
00:55:54,780 --> 00:55:57,890
I can't, so I'm going
to go. So, um...

951
00:55:57,940 --> 00:55:59,740
Right, here I go.

952
00:56:04,500 --> 00:56:06,570
Oh, it's tensioning up.

953
00:56:09,620 --> 00:56:11,490
This is OK so far.

954
00:56:15,300 --> 00:56:17,940
Oh! There it is.

955
00:56:19,860 --> 00:56:22,250
Oh, my God!

956
00:56:22,300 --> 00:56:26,300
Oh! Oh-ho-ho! Oh!

957
00:56:31,540 --> 00:56:33,650
I know it's slow.

958
00:56:33,700 --> 00:56:37,580
Any faster and I risk burning out
all the winch motors and things.

959
00:56:38,740 --> 00:56:42,380
Plus, there was an issue with
the face of the dam itself.

960
00:56:43,860 --> 00:56:47,570
The one on the advert was smooth
concrete, this is rough stone.

961
00:56:47,620 --> 00:56:50,090
I didn't take that into account.

962
00:56:52,300 --> 00:56:54,850
What I've got to do is
steer between these rocks

963
00:56:54,900 --> 00:56:56,650
where they stick out from the face.

964
00:56:56,700 --> 00:57:00,130
METALLIC GRINDING Oh! It's jerking.

965
00:57:00,180 --> 00:57:01,930
I'm having to read the surface.

966
00:57:01,980 --> 00:57:03,850
CLANG! Oh!

967
00:57:03,900 --> 00:57:05,370
CABLE GROANS

968
00:57:05,420 --> 00:57:09,620
This vertical off-roading
gave me another problem.

969
00:57:11,260 --> 00:57:16,290
Because the Land Rover is winching
itself up on its own winch,

970
00:57:16,340 --> 00:57:19,770
the cable has to feed
evenly onto the drum.

971
00:57:19,820 --> 00:57:23,020
If it doesn't do that,
everything gets ruined.

972
00:57:23,860 --> 00:57:29,210
I couldn't see the drum, so, up top,
the producers were spotting for me.

973
00:57:29,260 --> 00:57:31,730
Straighten up, please, Richard.

974
00:57:35,460 --> 00:57:36,930
Ah...

975
00:57:36,980 --> 00:57:38,660
Oh...

976
00:57:41,300 --> 00:57:42,570
Oh...

977
00:57:44,940 --> 00:57:48,210
Because it's so slow I've got time
to think about what would happen if...

978
00:57:48,260 --> 00:57:50,650
I can't, I daren't.
I am now terrified.

979
00:57:50,700 --> 00:57:53,890
I am now absolutely petrified.

980
00:57:53,940 --> 00:57:55,210
Oh...

981
00:57:57,860 --> 00:58:01,740
Past the halfway point it
started to get even worse.

982
00:58:03,380 --> 00:58:06,250
I can feel the front wheels
now going very light...

983
00:58:06,300 --> 00:58:10,850
because... where it goes concave,
where it bellies in like that...

984
00:58:10,900 --> 00:58:14,540
my winch cable is pulling the front
of the car off the ground. Oh!

985
00:58:16,100 --> 00:58:19,300
And I can't tell you
how horrible that feels.

986
00:58:19,900 --> 00:58:22,130
Oh-ho!

987
00:58:22,180 --> 00:58:24,330
Stop, stop, stop.

988
00:58:24,380 --> 00:58:25,890
I'm stopping, I'm stopping.

989
00:58:25,940 --> 00:58:27,680
ENGINE SHUTS OFF

990
00:58:30,780 --> 00:58:33,610
~ Honestly, mate, you've
got about 20 seconds, I'm
~ BLEEP
~ scared, OK?

991
00:58:33,660 --> 00:58:35,330
And I mean it.

992
00:58:36,860 --> 00:58:40,290
OK, take your mind off it, take
your mind off it. Um... this...

993
00:58:40,340 --> 00:58:42,250
THUMP! Ah!

994
00:58:42,300 --> 00:58:45,170
The water behind this dam
can supply Birmingham

995
00:58:45,220 --> 00:58:48,810
with 79 million gallons a day.

996
00:58:48,860 --> 00:58:50,890
~ Who gives a
~ BLEEP
~ right now?

997
00:58:50,940 --> 00:58:53,210
It's all right, we're good.

998
00:58:58,260 --> 00:59:00,460
It's really vertical now.

999
00:59:04,340 --> 00:59:05,610
Oh, God.

1000
00:59:05,660 --> 00:59:07,890
CABLE GROANS

1001
00:59:07,940 --> 00:59:09,610
I can hear the lines...

1002
00:59:09,660 --> 00:59:12,860
I can actually hear the
tension in that wire.

1003
00:59:15,980 --> 00:59:17,530
As I get to the top,

1004
00:59:17,580 --> 00:59:19,290
the cable becomes less strong.

1005
00:59:19,340 --> 00:59:22,090
Partly because, as well as the
weight of the Land Rover and me,

1006
00:59:22,140 --> 00:59:26,140
it has to be carrying the weight
of itself and the winch.

1007
00:59:28,340 --> 00:59:31,530
CABLE GROANS

1008
00:59:31,580 --> 00:59:35,490
Oh, God, I'm depending so much
on things made by other people.

1009
00:59:35,540 --> 00:59:39,730
Every single part now - the brake
that stops the winch feeding out,

1010
00:59:39,780 --> 00:59:42,020
the engine - everything.

1011
00:59:43,620 --> 00:59:46,250
In the face of unutterable terror

1012
00:59:46,300 --> 00:59:49,700
I was, finally, nearing the top.

1013
00:59:51,660 --> 00:59:55,160
We have nearly done this,
I've nearly cracked it.

1014
00:59:55,460 --> 00:59:57,930
200 feet of near vertical rock.

1015
01:00:03,380 --> 01:00:06,620
Just a few inches, another
few turns on the winch.

1016
01:00:11,100 --> 01:00:12,730
What a fantastic way...

1017
01:00:12,780 --> 01:00:15,090
to pay tribute...

1018
01:00:15,140 --> 01:00:17,970
to the car... What?

1019
01:00:18,020 --> 01:00:22,210
It was at this point the
producers broke the bad news.

1020
01:00:22,260 --> 01:00:25,090
Because of where the winch
cable was attached,

1021
01:00:25,140 --> 01:00:30,330
the Land Rover wouldn't be able to
climb over onto the flat dam top.

1022
01:00:30,380 --> 01:00:33,220
And this meant only one thing.

1023
01:00:35,220 --> 01:00:37,820
I'm going to have to go back down.

1024
01:00:38,460 --> 01:00:41,460
I'm going to have to
winch it down the dam.

1025
01:00:44,060 --> 01:00:46,060
I really need a piss!

1026
01:00:49,540 --> 01:00:51,580
CHEERING AND APPLAUSE

1027
01:00:53,660 --> 01:00:56,610
Thank you. It was nothing.

1028
01:00:56,660 --> 01:00:58,400
It was nothing.

1029
01:00:59,820 --> 01:01:03,210
So... you failed.

1030
01:01:03,260 --> 01:01:04,810
Well, I almost got to the top.

1031
01:01:04,860 --> 01:01:07,250
Yeah, but then you just came
straight back down again.

1032
01:01:07,300 --> 01:01:10,530
I'm sorry, Hammond, if I said, "I'm
going to drive to Bristol," and then

1033
01:01:10,580 --> 01:01:14,570
got NEARLY to Bristol and came home
again, that's NOT going to Bristol.

1034
01:01:14,620 --> 01:01:17,490
Look, the main thing is I
gave the Land Rover Defender

1035
01:01:17,540 --> 01:01:21,290
~ a fitting sendoff.
~ Yeah, but they're working
on a new Defender now

1036
01:01:21,340 --> 01:01:24,210
and it looks EXACTLY
the same as the old one.

1037
01:01:24,260 --> 01:01:28,730
So you said you'd drive to the
top of a dam, which you didn't,

1038
01:01:28,780 --> 01:01:32,690
to pay tribute to a car that you
said was about to die, but it's not.

1039
01:01:32,740 --> 01:01:34,170
Yeah.

1040
01:01:34,220 --> 01:01:37,930
Well, that means you're a liar and
you've completely wasted our time.

1041
01:01:37,980 --> 01:01:39,610
Yeah.

1042
01:01:39,660 --> 01:01:41,770
And on that bombshell, I'm
afraid it's time to end.

1043
01:01:41,820 --> 01:01:44,490
Next week normal service is resumed.

1044
01:01:44,540 --> 01:01:46,970
James and I have a lot
of crashes on purpose.

1045
01:01:47,020 --> 01:01:50,100
Hopefully we shall see you then.
Thank you for watching, good night!

